  "text": "Photoperiodic and clock regulation of dmpi8 splicing. We previously showed that in wild-type flies entrained by standard 12-h light-12-h dark cycles (12:12LD; where ZT0 is lights-on), cold temperatures stimulate the relative splicing of dmpi8 (i.e., relative molar ratio of type BЈ to type A per variants), which underlies the earlier daily upswing in total per mRNA abundance and higher peak values (36) (see also Fig. 7A and B). Importantly, it is the more-rapid accumulation phase of per mRNA that contributes to the advanced evening activity of Drosophila on cold days [CITATION_1] . In temperate regions, low daily temperatures are normally associated with short day lengths.",
